														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3115618">
									

<p>I just finished 1636: The Ottoman Onslaught, the&#8230; latest? second latest? book in the 1632/Ring of Fire series. They're&#8230; mostly popcorn reading for me, but it's the only series I've stuck with this long.</p>
<p>It's a series of books about a &quot;modern&quot; (at the time of writing, 2000) West Virginia town being transported back in time to Germany in the Thirty Years War, and then about 25 novels/anthologies about the political and military aftermath. One neat thing is that they're basically half or more fan-written/co-written. The first one is free online, because they know how to hook you: <a href="http://www.baen.com/1632.html">http://www.baen.com/1632.html</a></p>

							</div>

								
					
