			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3133587">
									

<p>Holy shit, that's popcorn reading for you? I haven't heard of this, will check out the link, thanks, always looking for new material to read, but 25 novels is pretty overwhelming, fan-written or not. But hey, if they know how to hook you&#8230; I'd also consider 2000 to be modern, although yeah, I guess it's almost twenty years ago now.</p>
<p>That Witcher introduction book I'm reading is called The Last Wish, and so far I'm liking it better than Blood of Elves. Blood almost reminded me of a Foundation Asimov book where most of it's told through dialogue, only pulling it off not nearly as successful as the Foundation series.</p>

