<p>Finished The Last Wish, the first witcher book. It was better than Blood of Elves, which is the first part of a trilogy. This one is a stand-alone, and it's more a collection of short stories woven together in a Bradbury-esque way, rather than a singular narrative.</p>
<p>I'm almost done with Treasure Island, by Robert Louis Stevenson. I know it's considered a kid's book, but I've never read it before, and figure I'd add another notch to my classics list.</p>
