			<div class="content" id="post-content-3569099">
									

<p>Reading the Dresden Files by Jim Butcher, love the series.</p>
<p>Filled to the brim with magic, mystery and supernatural conflict. Currently I've finished all but one and the one that I haven't read is the 2nd in the series 'Fool Moon'. I'm sure judging from the ending of the latest book the series is still being written and isn't done.</p>
<p>Basically the books involve a wizard named Harry Dresden who gets himself throat deep in conflict that nobody should be able to resolve, but he resolves it somehow (probably because of all the supernatural forces such as archangels, gods and other powerful entities helping him).</p>
<p>The series actually inspires some of what I write up here. See mostly, I like to keep myself as far away from religious content as possible. But the thing is, I've never really realized that there can be so much tales and articles that could explore the narrative that it is actually quite hard to not write about it. Among other little things that inspires my writing.</p>
<p>That's basically it :P</p>

